data.text:
May 15, 2003

MANHATTAN, KS. -- The University of North Carolina men's golf team finished the first round of the NCAA Central Regional tied for fourth place with North Carolina State University with a team total of 283. The University of Illinois leads the opening round with a 13-under-par 275 total. Southern Methodist is second at 277 and the University of Kentucky follows in third at 280.

Jason Moon of North Carolina State leads the Regional in individual scoring after firing a six-under-par 66, while four golfers are tied second at 67. They include James Lapp and Patrick Nagle of Illinois, Matt Kohn of Kentucky and James Lepp of Southern Methodist. UNC golfer Dustin Bray along with seven others are tied for sixth at four-under-par 68.

Other Tar Heels participating in the Regional include Kevin Silva who carded a two-under-par 70, Richard Treis shot even-par 72, Jeremy Elliott had a one-over-par 73, and Ramon Bescansa followed with a 75.

The 2003 NCAA Central Regional in being hosted by Kansas State University. The 54 hole tournament is being contested at the Par-72, 7228-yard Colbert Hills Golf Course. For information on Tee Times and live scoring go to Golfstat.com.
